CBRE is pleased to be exclusively appointed on the sale of 29-31 Waldheim Road, Bayswater. 

The property presents a significant landholding which has dual street access to Waldheim Road and Ricdanic Drive. The low site coverage allows owner occupiers or developers future expansion (STCA) or ample hardstand/yard all within 2.6km* of M3 Eastlink.

Surrounding local occupiers include Confoil, Camerons Transport, and Emerson Automation Solutions.

Location Details:
+ M3 Eastlink 2.6km*
+ Mountain Highway 111m*
+ Stud Road 175m*
+ Bayswater Railway Station 1.67km*
+ Westfield Knox 2.95km*

Property Details:
+ Offered with vacant possession
+ Industrial 1 Zone
+ Total building area 4,788sqm*
+ Total land area 14,631sqm*
+ Dual street frontages to Waldheim Road and Ricdanic Drive

For further information on the sale of 29-31 Waldheim Road please contact exclusive marketing agents Joe Brzezek or Sasan Misaghian from CBRE.

*approx.

CBRE Australian Healthcare & Social Infrastructure are pleased to offer for sale 1/664 Mountain Highway, Bayswater – An established Day Hospital and Specialist Centre offered with vacant possession.

With impeccably maintained existing improvements in-line with existing day procedure accreditation standards, the subject property can be occupied, refurbished or repositioned (STCA). Immediate cross flow demand across the entire Wantirna health precinct is substantial with Knox Private Hospital providing it’s medical services to over 1.2 million people per annum.

OVERVIEW

+ Ground floor day hospital of 269sqm* PLUS on-site parking for 10 vehicles

+ Offered with Vacant Possession, Zoned “Commercial 1”

+ Currently utilised for 6 beds plus consultation appointments and permitted for speciality health services

+ High quality existing fit out allowing immediate occupation - 4 consulting rooms; operating theatre; recovery room plus anaesthetic room

+ Significant exposure to the highly trafficked Mountain Highway allowing strong promotional / signage placement opportunity

LOCATION

+ Positioned within the VPA planned Wantirna Health Precinct and less than 3 minutes* from the Knox Private Hospital (3km) one of the largest private hospitals in Australia and Wantirna Health Hospital

+ Highly favourable demographic trends with the Bayswater population expected to increase by 46% by 2041

+ Within walking distance to Bayswater Woolworth shopping centre (70m*), Bayswater Coles and shopping retail precinct only 150m* and Bayswater Train Station 300m*
